%S A272003 2,9,1,0,0,6,0,9,3
%N A272003 Decimal expansion of Cp(2), the molar specific heat of an diatomic ideal gas at constant pressure.
%C A272003 Also the decimal expansion of Cv(3), the molar specific heat of a triatomic gas at constant volume.
%C A272003 The molar specific heat of an n-atomic gas at constant pressure and volume can be calculated respectively with the following formulae:
%C A272003 - Cv(n) = (n + 1/2) R;
%C A272003 - Cp(n) = (n + 3/2) R;
%C A272003 Where R = Cp(n) - Cv(n) = Cp(n) - Cp(n-1) = A081822 is IUPAC's value of the gas constant.
%F A272003 Cp(2) = (2 + 3/2) * R = 7/2 * A081822.
%F A272003 Cp(2) = Cp(1) + R = Cv(2) + R = A272002 + A081822.
%e A272003 Cp(2) = 29.1006093 J mol^-1 K^-1.
%Y A272003 Cf. A081822, A272001, A272002.
